CatDescriptText: Mrs. James Burnette, 3516 East Court, Broadhead, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 5, 1958, pg. 2 with question: "Which do you think people give priority recognition to, the acquisition of money or achievement?" answer reads: "I think that the majority of people give the priority recognition to the man who has the money. The possession of money by a person seems to give more impression to him than what he is doing otherwise.  The person who has money, people seem to pay more attention to and to be more greatly influenced by."
